parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the carburetor can cause the vehicle to stall or surge forward while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or surges forward while driving
hesitation or sudden loss of power
carbon buildup on the intake valve.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: High concentrations of hydrogen chloride in the vehicle can cause corrosion and damage to internal components, leading to premature wear and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: High concentration of hydrogen chloride in the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Leading to Vehicle Fire
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause a vehicle fire, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke or flames coming from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: stalling in traffic or while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clogged valves can cause the engine to surge or stop, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stalling in traffic.
The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, which can lead to accidents, especially if it occurs while driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls at any speed
the vehicle hesitates when starting up again

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of power and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
